body_html:
Wow! Tensorboard is so amazing.

Ran into some issues using the example you've provided with the docker install, not sure if I'm the only one. but fwiw, here they are:

Web server couldn't find some icons:
No such file or directory: '/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/tensorflow/tensorboard/lib/svg/summary-icon.svg' on path /usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/tensorflow/tensorboard/lib/svg/summary-icon.svg

Also, when I click on the various icons, I'm not seeing much in the way of data. Is that right? Maybe it is :D For example, test namespace ->

test​/ScalarSummary

Operation: ScalarSummary
Attributes (1)
T
{"type":"DT_FLOAT"}
Inputs (0)
Outputs (0)

or on Wx_b namespace and then Histogram:

HistogramSummary_2

Operation: HistogramSummary
Attributes (0)
Inputs (0)
Outputs (0)

The histograms and events tabs seem to be showing up properly. Cheers
